title: Cumulus
description: Detached clouds, generally dense and with sharp outlines, developing vertically in the form of rising mounds, domes or towers, of which the bulging upper part often resembles a cauliflower. The sunlit parts of these clouds are mostly brilliant white; their base is relatively dark and nearly horizontal.
subject: Meteorology
creator: Leobardo Óscar Alcántara Ocaña

title: Cumulonimbus
description: Heavy and dense cloud, with a considerable vertical extent, in the form of a mountain or huge towers. At least part of its upper portion is usually smooth, or fibrous or striated, and nearly always flattened; this part often spreads out in the shape of an anvil or vast plume.

creator: Leobardo Óscar Alcántara Ocaña

title: Stratocumulus
description: Grey or whitish, or both grey and whitish, patch, sheet or layer of cloud that almost always has dark parts, composed of tessellations, rounded masses, rolls, etc., which are non-fibrous (except for virga) and which may or may not be merged; most of the regularly arranged small elements have an apparent width of more than 5
creator: Leobardo Óscar Alcántara Ocaña

description: Grey or whitish, or both grey and whitish, patch, sheet or layer of cloud that almost always has dark parts, composed of tessellations, rounded masses, rolls, etc., which are non-fibrous (except for virga) and which may or may not be merged; most of the regularly arranged small elements have an apparent width of more than 6

title: Cumulus
description: Detached clouds, generally dense and with sharp outlines, developing vertically in the form of rising mounds, domes or towers, of which the bulging upper part often resembles a cauliflower. The sunlit parts of these clouds are mostly brilliant white; their base is relatively dark and nearly horizontal.
creator: Leobardo Óscar Alcántara Ocaña

title: Cirrocumulus

creator: Leobardo Óscar Alcántara Ocaña

Low: From the Earth’s surface to 2 km
(0 – 6 500ft)
accessory: Detached clouds, generally dense and with sharp outlines, developing vertically in the form of rising mounds, domes or towers, of which the bulging upper part often resembles a cauliflower.
description: Guadalajara Jalisco, México
creator: http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC/1.0/
